modules.description: Parses and generates HTTP cookies from request headers and response headers, validating attributes like domain, path, and expiration. Works with strings, dates, and structured cookie data including name-value pairs and attributes. Ensures compliance with RFC 6265 and related standards when handling cookie transmission and storage.

The module enables parsing, serializing, and manipulating HTTP cookies, along with handling date-time values to ensure compliance with RFC 6265 and RFC 1123 standards. It works with cookie records containing attributes like domain, path, expiration, and secure flags, supporting immutable updates to modify these properties. Use cases include constructing valid Cookie headers for requests, processing Set-Cookie headers in responses, and enforcing secure cookie policies in web applications.
